Italian carrier buys four more ATR turbo planes . Aero International ( Regional ) said at the Paris air show on Thursday it had signed deals to sell four ATR turboprop aircraft to Italian regional carrier Air Dolomiti . The sale includes three of the most recent model , the ATR 72 - 210A fitted with 64 seats , and one ATR 42 - 500 . It brings to 13 the number of ATR aircraft operated by Air Dolomiti , whose routes include city - hopping flights between northern Italy and southern Germany or France . 
